Resolves environment and bind-list details for the cage runtime: toolchain directories, secret masks, tool binaries, and the full replacement environment used with `bwrap --clearenv`. Split out of `run.rs` purely to stay under a file-length tier — no independent responsibility beyond that.

`detect_secret_masks(root: &Path) -> Vec<String>` checks for `.env` and `.git/config` under `root` and returns the ones that exist, to be masked even though the workspace is writable. `bound_tool_dirs() -> Vec<PathBuf>` combines Rust toolchain homes (`CARGO_HOME`/`RUSTUP_HOME`, defaulting to `~/.cargo`/`~/.rustup` when unset, only if the resolved directory exists) with `CTX_CAGE_EXTRA_PATH` entries (colon-separated, non-directories dropped). This list feeds both the bwrap RO-bind list and `PATH` construction in `base_env` — **these two call sites must stay in sync**; drifting the resolution logic in one without the other silently breaks either bind visibility or PATH lookup.

`tool_binds(r: &Resolved, prep: &Prep) -> Vec<(PathBuf, String)>` always binds `ctx-verify`, `ctx-context`, `ctx-scan` under `/cage/bin`; when `prep.claude` is `Some`, it additionally binds the claude binary twice (once on PATH, once at `CAGE_LOCAL_CLAUDE`, the installer-check path claude expects under its cage `HOME`) plus the RO subscription credential. `claude_rw_binds(prep: &Prep)` binds only the synthesized `~/.claude.json` read-write, since claude rewrites it at runtime.

`cage_env(r: &Resolved) -> Vec<(String, String)>` builds the full replacement environment for `--clearenv`. It deliberately never sets `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` — auth flows through the bound subscription credential instead, and setting a key would trigger claude's interactive "use detected API key?" prompt, breaking headless runs. For `Mode::Task`, it injects `CTX_TASK_BRIEF`; for billed modes (`mode_is_billed`), it injects `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` pointing at `CAGE_BASE_URL`. `base_env` builds the mode-independent baseline: PATH is assembled in a fixed order (cage bin, cargo bin, extra dirs, then `/usr/bin:/bin`), plus `HOME=/tmp`, `USER=cage`, `LANG=C.UTF-8`, `TERM` (inherited from host or defaulted to `xterm-256color`, to preserve Claude Code TUI color), `TASK`, and `CARGO_NET_OFFLINE=true`.